<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1436,1518,1940]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
TYPE LOCALITY. Originally stated as “ 
<collectingCountry box="[585,656,1590,1615]" name="Iran" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Persia</collectingCountry>
or Baluchistan”; restricted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Anderson, S. C. &amp; Leviton, A. E." box="[1007,1338,1590,1615]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="499 - 534" refId="ref45420" refString="Anderson, S. C. &amp; Leviton, A. E. (1966 b) A review of the genus Ophiomorus with description of three new forms. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 33, 499 - 534." type="journal article" year="1966">Anderson &amp; Leviton (1966b)</bibRefCitation>
to Chah Bahar [Chabahar], Sistan and Baluchistan Prov., 
<collectingCountry box="[701,750,1627,1650]" name="Iran" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Iran</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1436,1518,1940]" box="[151,616,1662,1687]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
DISTRIBUTION. SE 
<collectingCountry box="[365,410,1663,1686]" name="Iran" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Iran</collectingCountry>
and SW 
<collectingCountry box="[514,613,1662,1687]" name="Pakistan" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1436,1518,1940]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
DISTRIBUTION IN 
<collectingCountry box="[359,415,1699,1722]" name="Iran" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">IRAN</collectingCountry>
. 
<figureCitation box="[435,536,1699,1724]" captionStart="FIGURES 128–133. 128" captionStartId="93.[151,264,1557,1580]" captionTargetBox="[171,1416,213,1516]" captionTargetId="figure-79@93.[151,1436,193,1536]" captionTargetPageId="93" captionText="FIGURES 128–133. 128. Ablepharus pannonicus. 129. Chalcides ocellatus. 130. Eumeces schneiderii. Red symbols represent records of E. s. princeps, blue of E. s. zarudnyi and blue square denotes its type locality, violet question mark indicates dubious data for E. blythianus. 131. Eurylepis taeniolatus. 132. Ophiomorus blanfordii. 133. Ophiomorus brevipes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4929775" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4929775/files/figure.png" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Fig. 132</figureCitation>
. Known with certainty only from the 
<typeStatus box="[992,1040,1699,1723]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">type</typeStatus>
locality, although there are more mentions of this species but without exact locality data (
<bibRefCitation author="Boulenger, G. A." box="[780,964,1734,1759]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" refId="ref47622" refString="Boulenger, G. A. (1887) Catalogue of the lizards in the British Museum (Natural History). Vol. III. Lacertidae, Gerrhosauridae, Scincidae, Anelytropidae, Dibamidae, Chamaeleontidae. Trustees of the British Museum, London, 575 pp." type="book" year="1887">Boulenger 1887</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Werner, F." box="[976,1127,1734,1759]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="191 - 220" refId="ref67401" refString="Werner, F. (1917) Reptilien aus Persien (Provinz Fars). Verhandlungen der Zoologisch-Botanishen Gesellschaft in Wien, 67, 191 - 220." type="journal article" year="1917">Werner 1917</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1436,1518,1940]" box="[151,896,1771,1796]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
HABITAT. Coastal sand dunes with sparse vegetation (
<bibRefCitation author="Khan, M. S." box="[754,884,1771,1796]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" refId="ref56151" refString="Khan, M. S. (2006) Amphibians and Reptiles of Pakistan. Krieger Publishing Company, Malabar, Florida, 311 pp." type="book" year="2006">Khan 2006</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1436,1518,1940]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
REMARKS. Boulenger in his original description used the spelling ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boulenger" authorityYear="1887" box="[903,1015,1806,1831]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Ophiomorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="blanfordii">
<emphasis box="[903,1015,1806,1831]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">blanfordii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ with a double ‘i’, hence the spelling ‘ 
<taxonomicName box="[160,264,1843,1868]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Acanthodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="blanfordi">
<emphasis box="[160,264,1843,1868]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">blanfordi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ used by many authors (
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, M. A." box="[544,679,1843,1868]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" refId="ref65609" refString="Smith, M. A. (1935) The fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. Reptilia and Amphibia. Vol. II. Sauria. Taylor and Francis, Ltd., Red Lion Court, Fleet Street, London, 440 pp. [Reprint Edition 1974, Today and Tomorrow's Printers and Publishers]" type="book" year="1935">Smith 1935</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Anderson, S. C. &amp; Leviton, A. E." box="[692,1006,1843,1868]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="499 - 534" refId="ref45420" refString="Anderson, S. C. &amp; Leviton, A. E. (1966 b) A review of the genus Ophiomorus with description of three new forms. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 33, 499 - 534." type="journal article" year="1966">Anderson &amp; Leviton 1966b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Anderson, S. C." box="[1018,1194,1843,1868]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" refId="ref45318" refString="Anderson, S. C. (1999) The lizards of Iran. Society for the Study of Amphibians and Reptiles, Oxford, Ohio, 442 pp." type="book" year="1999">Anderson 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Khan, M. S." box="[1206,1333,1843,1868]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" refId="ref56151" refString="Khan, M. S. (2006) Amphibians and Reptiles of Pakistan. Krieger Publishing Company, Malabar, Florida, 311 pp." type="book" year="2006">Khan 2006</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sindaco, R. &amp; Jeremcenko, V. K." pageId="44" pageNumber="45" refId="ref65138" refString="Sindaco, R. &amp; Jeremcenko, V. K. (2008) The reptiles of the Western Palearctic. 1. Annotated checklist and distributional atlas of the turtles, crocodiles, amphisbaenians and lizards of Europe, North Africa, Middle East and Central Asia. Monografie della Societas Herpetologica Italica, Edizioni Belvedere, 579 pp." type="book" year="2008">Sindaco &amp; Jeremčenko 2008</bibRefCitation>
) is incorrect.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
